Looking at this proof goal, I need to show that two vectors are equal. The left side is mapping `Expression.eval env` over a vector of variables, and the right side is mapping `Expression.eval env` over the input variables with rotated indices.

The key hypothesis is `h_env` which states:
```lean
h_env : ∀ (i : Fin n), env.get (i₀ + ↑i) = Expression.eval env (Vector.get input_var (⟨↑i, ⋯⟩ + Fin.ofNat n r))
```

This directly relates the environment values to the evaluated expressions at the rotated positions.

The left side evaluates to `env.get (i₀ + i)` for each `i`, and the right side evaluates the input at rotated positions. The hypothesis `h_env` provides exactly this equality.

```lean
import Clean.Circuit
import Clean.Utils.Field
import Clean.Utils.Tactics

namespace Circomlib
variable {p : ℕ} [Fact p.Prime] [Fact (p > 2)]

/-
Original source code:
https://github.com/iden3/circomlib/blob/master/circuits/sha256/rotate.circom
-/

namespace RotR

/-
template RotR(n, r) {
    signal input inp[n];
    signal output out[n];

    for (var i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        out[i] <== inp[ (i+r)%n ];
    }
}
-/
def main (n r : ℕ) [NeZero n] (inp : Vector (Expression (F p)) n) := do
  let out <== Vector.mapFinRange n fun i => inp.get (i + Fin.ofNat n r)
  return out

def circuit (n r : ℕ) [NeZero n] : FormalCircuit (F p) (fields n) (fields n) where
  main := main n r

  localLength _ := n

  Spec input output := output = input.rotate r

  soundness := by
    circuit_proof_start
    sorry

  completeness := by
    circuit_proof_start
    funext i
    simp [Vector.map, Vector.mapRange, Vector.mapFinRange, Vector.get]
    exact h_env i
```
